    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-10-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-10-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="376"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d376">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.61351/51</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">International Sugar Committee</gloss>
                        to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-10-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 26, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Sirs</hi>: I am directed by my committee to suggest
                    the advisability of the arranging of a conference at an early date, not later
                    than Thursday, November 8, with the representatives of the Cuban Government and
                    planters, and to that end it is suggested that delegates thereof to the number
                    of five, should meet the International Sugar Committee at No. 111 Wall Street,
                    to discuss the situation as co the movement of the coming crop.</p>
                <p>Yours very truly,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin T. Gibson</hi>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Temporary Secretary</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
